HEADWORD: Cenatory
<hw>Cen"a*to*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>cenatorius</ets>, fr. <ets>cenare</ets> to dine, sup, fr.
<ets>cena</ets>, <ets>coena</ets>, dinner, supper.]</ety> <def>Of or
pertaining to dinner or supper.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The Romans washed, were anointed, and wore a <qex>cenatory</qex>
garment.</q> <rj><qau>Sir T. Browne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cenobite</ent>⟦br⟧
